verbs.description: outspin (third-person singular simple present outspins, present participle outspinning, simple past and past participle outspun)

examples: […]  again and again as if she could not tear herself away, yet each time dancing farther forward, swaying to and fro. Finally, her arms raised, she began twirling around, faster and faster, as if she were trying to outspin time itself.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To exceed in spinning; exceed in spinning thread.
examples: As if we could outspin the Fatal Sisters.
